# Implement the protocol agents ({{ ip }}, phase 2)

## Precondition

Phase 1 done: `make -C sim compile` passes against the real RTL (no DUT stub
note). See `connect-dut.prompt.md`.

## Goal

Replace every `TODO(protocol)` stub with the real protocol logic so the smoke
test exercises the actual DUT interfaces.

## Relevant files (per agent)

{% for a in agents %}
* `agents/{{ a.name }}_agent/{{ ip }}_{{ a.name }}_seq_item.sv` — real transaction fields + constraints
* `agents/{{ a.name }}_agent/{{ ip }}_{{ a.name }}_driver.sv` — pin-level driving in `drive_item()` / `drive_idle()`
* `agents/{{ a.name }}_agent/{{ ip }}_{{ a.name }}_monitor.sv` — transaction reconstruction in `run_phase()`
* `agents/{{ a.name }}_agent/{{ ip }}_{{ a.name }}_if.sv` — signals, clocking blocks, protocol assertions
{% endfor %}
{% for v in vips %}
* `vip/{{ v.name }}_vip/` — Cadence {{ v.title }} VIP wrapper: follow the TODO(vip)
  markers (import the VIP package, create/program its config from
  `{{ ip }}_{{ v.name }}_vip_cfg`, forward monitor traffic + sequencer). Activate the
  compile lines in `sim/vip_{{ v.protocol }}.f` — requires `$CDN_VIP_ROOT`.
{% endfor %}

## Rules

* Drivers/monitors use ONLY `cfg.vif` (set through `{{ ip }}_env_cfg`) — never
  fetch interfaces from the config_db or reference the tb hierarchy.
* Keep passive-mode behavior intact: monitor-only when
  `cfg.is_active == UVM_PASSIVE` (drivers/sequencers are not built).
* Monitors must reconstruct transactions from pins (not echo driver state),
  so passive SoC reuse observes real bus traffic.

## Commands

```bash
make -C sim compile
make -C sim run TEST={{ ip }}_smoke_test
make -C sim run TEST={{ ip }}_smoke_test XRUN_OPTS=+{{ IP }}_PASSIVE=all   # reuse check
```

## Done when

`make -C sim run TEST={{ ip }}_smoke_test` completes with `UVM_ERROR : 0` and
the scoreboard reports observed transactions; the `+{{ IP }}_PASSIVE=all` run
also passes (no stimulus, no errors). Then continue with
`write-tests.prompt.md`.
